    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-14T18:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-14T18:14:00-05:00" n="387"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d387">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/346.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-14T18:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 14, 1914, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Government officers report bombardment and burning of Esmeraldas on February
                    11th. American Minister at Lima inquires by cable whether the Department will
                    send cruiser to Esmeraldas and if so, when. He expresses anxiety for cable
                    operatives. Matters are evidently in bad condition there. My inability to hear
                    from our Consul makes me fear for his safety. I think cruiser should be sent
                    there immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
